{"tid":883164,"cid":5,"subCid":0,"title":"侵侵計劃簽行政手令，停止雙非美籍 BB","createTime":"2018-10-30T15:28:58.000Z","updateTime":"2018-10-30T15:52:00.000Z","uid":130105,"like":15,"dislike":0,"uniUserReply":4,"replies":[{"pid":"1970d08a25e8d3464ee6b11c1b1fb874bc5d1c8b","tid":883164,"uid":130105,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-10-30T15:28:58.000Z","msg":"今次真係唔得了 <img src=\"/assets/faces/lomoji/32.png\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/lomoji/32.png\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/lomoji/32.png\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/lomoji/32.png\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <br />\n<br />\n=================<br />\n<ul><br />\n&bull;President said he wants to sign an executive order ending birthright citizenship<br />\n&bull;Trump said the current policy is 'ridiculous. It's ridiculous. And it has to end' <br />\n&bull;Debate over whether he can change meaning of Constitution's 14th Amendment<br />\n&bull;Trump believes he can alter the government's interpretation on his own<br />\n&bull;Amendment says it only applies to people 'subject to the jurisdiction' of the U.S. <br />\n&bull;Bombshell comes a week before mid-term elections and amid national panic after a second migrant caravan heading for the U.S. crossed into Mexico<br />\n</ul><br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2018/10/30/11/5569260-6332713-image-m-21_1540898638342.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fi.dailymail.co.uk%2F1s%2F2018%2F10%2F30%2F11%2F5569260-6332713-image-m-21_1540898638342.jpg&h=77374fe4&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n Donald Trump plans to revoke the citizenship rights of children born to non-citizens and illegal immigrants in the US<br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2018/10/30/11/5555578-6332713-The_second_group_back_at_the_Guatemalan_frontier_has_been_more_u-a-10_1540897594489.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fi.dailymail.co.uk%2F1s%2F2018%2F10%2F30%2F11%2F5555578-6332713-The_second_group_back_at_the_Guatemalan_frontier_has_been_more_u-a-10_1540897594489.jpg&h=176b380f&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n It comes two weeks before mid-term elections and after a second migrant caravan (pictured) crossed into Mexico on Monday<br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2018/10/30/11/5549836-6332713-The_migrants_were_met_by_hundreds_of_federal_officers_in_riot_ge-a-11_1540897597377.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fi.dailymail.co.uk%2F1s%2F2018%2F10%2F30%2F11%2F5549836-6332713-The_migrants_were_met_by_hundreds_of_federal_officers_in_riot_ge-a-11_1540897597377.jpg&h=d090fc4e&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n The migrants were met by hundreds of federal officers in riot gear on the river bank. It followed a night of violence that left one Central American dead <br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2015/08/19/17/2B7F421300000578-3203645-image-a-19_1440001939095.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fi.dailymail.co.uk%2Fi%2Fpix%2F2015%2F08%2F19%2F17%2F2B7F421300000578-3203645-image-a-19_1440001939095.jpg&h=d2aa8458&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\nCONSTITUTIONAL SCHOLAR: Donald Trump insists the question of 'birthright citizenship' is open to interpretation<br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2018/10/30/13/5572386-0-FILE_In_this_March_23_2016_photo_the_Constitution_is_held_by_a_m-a-2_1540904684911.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fi.dailymail.co.uk%2F1s%2F2018%2F10%2F30%2F13%2F5572386-0-FILE_In_this_March_23_2016_photo_the_Constitution_is_held_by_a_m-a-2_1540904684911.jpg&h=3d0ebe67&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2018/10/30/11/5551650-6332713-The_second_migrant_caravan_including_members_believed_to_be_carr-a-14_1540897601719.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fi.dailymail.co.uk%2F1s%2F2018%2F10%2F30%2F11%2F5551650-6332713-The_second_migrant_caravan_including_members_believed_to_be_carr-a-14_1540897601719.jpg&h=8686ffda&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n The second migrant caravan, including members believed to be carrying bombs and guns, crossed into Mexico on Monday despite a huge police presence. Cops are seen allowing some of the migrants on the banks of the Suchiate River after the arduous crossing, but they were stopped from moving any further<br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2018/10/30/11/5555596-6332713-Central_American_migrants_walk_along_the_highway_near_of_Ciudad_-a-16_1540897604700.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fi.dailymail.co.uk%2F1s%2F2018%2F10%2F30%2F11%2F5555596-6332713-Central_American_migrants_walk_along_the_highway_near_of_Ciudad_-a-16_1540897604700.jpg&h=3331d51a&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n Central American migrants walk along the highway near of Ciudad Hidalgo after crossing to Mexico from Guatemala willing to reach the U.S.<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://videos.dailymail.co.uk/video/mol/2018/10/29/7334397981179596400/1024x576_MP4_7334397981179596400.mp4\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fvideos.dailymail.co.uk%2Fvideo%2Fmol%2F2018%2F10%2F29%2F7334397981179596400%2F1024x576_MP4_7334397981179596400.mp4&d=GeIUBdKxD6J9w2hxUWaCUDPUa9iY%2BpOmOVTB4fMSqaQ%3D&h=26bb87da\" target=\"_blank\">https://videos.dailymail.co.uk/video/mol/2018/10/29/7334397981179596400/1024x576_MP4_7334397981179596400.mp4</a><br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://videos.dailymail.co.uk/video/mol/2017/03/23/3293549489518890181/1024x576_MP4_3293549489518890181.mp4\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fvideos.dailymail.co.uk%2Fvideo%2Fmol%2F2017%2F03%2F23%2F3293549489518890181%2F1024x576_MP4_3293549489518890181.mp4&d=GeIUBdKxD6J9w2hxUWaCUDPUa9iY%2BpOmOVTB4fMSqaQ%3D&h=0509b8ca\" target=\"_blank\">https://videos.dailymail.co.uk/video/mol/2017/03/23/3293549489518890181/1024x576_MP4_3293549489518890181.mp4</a><br />\n<br />\nsource: